---
import ClerriLayout from '../../layouts/ClerriLayout.astro';
---
<ClerriLayout title="Ad Creative & Targeting" section="ad-strategy">

<div class="page-head">
  <div class="page-eyebrow">06 · Creative & Targeting</div>
  <h1 class="page-title">What hooks them, <em>what they ignore.</em></h1>
  <p class="page-sub">Three personas (independent owner, group practice operator, DSO executive). Each with pain hooks, ad formats, targeting layers, and the creative tropes that work — plus the ones that look "too B2B SaaS" and turn dentists off instantly.</p>
</div>

<div class="page-body">

  <div class="progress-track"><div class="progress-fill" data-progress-fill="ad-strategy"></div></div>
  <p class="mono" style="font-size:0.75rem;color:var(--muted)">Progress: <span data-progress-here="ad-strategy">0 / 0</span> creative tasks completed</p>

  <!-- WHAT WORKS / WHAT FAILS -->
  <h2>What works in dental advertising <em>(and what dies).</em></h2>
  <div class="grid-2">
    <div class="callout mint">
      <div class="lbl">✓ Works — dentists trust this</div>
      <ul style="font-size:0.9rem;padding-left:1rem;margin:0">
        <li><strong>Dentist-on-camera testimonials</strong> (Brett Wells/DentalHQ pattern)</li>
        <li>"Without insurance vs. with our plan" dollar-savings carousels with specific numbers</li>
        <li>Glenn Vo-style "deals with promo codes" social posts</li>
        <li>Before/after revenue dashboard screenshots</li>
        <li><strong>Specific dollar amounts</strong> ("Jenny saved $938 last year"), specific patient counts</li>
        <li>Real practice staff in shots — owner spouse, hygienist, front office</li>
        <li>Dentist-led webinars (peer-to-peer credibility)</li>
        <li>Earned PR in dental publications (Becker's, GDN, DPR)</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
    <div class="callout wine">
      <div class="lbl">✗ Avoid — instantly reads "outsider"</div>
      <ul style="font-size:0.9rem;padding-left:1rem;margin:0">
        <li>Stock-photo handshake images</li>
        <li>Gradient SaaS hero cards with abstract icons</li>
        <li>"Transform your practice" abstractions</li>
        <li>AI/ML jargon without specific outcome</li>
        <li>Generic "platform" language with no proof points</li>
        <li>Vendor-speak ("schedule a demo to learn more")</li>
        <li>Tech-bro aesthetic — chrome, neon gradients, isometric illustrations</li>
        <li>Anything that looks like it could be selling SaaS to lawyers or accountants</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- PERSONA 1: INDEPENDENT OWNER -->
  <h2>Persona 01 · <em>Independent Practice Owner</em></h2>
  <div class="card">
    <p><strong>Profile:</strong> 1-3 location solo or small group. Owner-dentist still chairside. Practice manager often spouse or long-tenured staff. Decisions made over kitchen table or short meetings. Time-poor, suspicious of vendor jargon.</p>

    <h4>Pain hooks (lead with these, not "we offer X")</h4>
    <ul style="padding-left:1rem">
      <li>"PPO write-offs ate <strong>32% of your hygiene revenue</strong> last year."</li>
      <li>"Your hygienist's chair sits 18% empty. Members fill it <strong>4.3x more</strong> than uninsured walk-ins."</li>
      <li>"Stop chasing $89 cleanings. Start owning <strong>$30 MRR per patient</strong>."</li>
      <li>"30% of dentists dropped insurance last year. Here's where they went."</li>
      <li>"Lifetime PPO write-offs: $3-6M. That's a vacation home you'll never buy."</li>
    </ul>

    <h4>Ad formats &amp; CPC efficiency</h4>
    <div class="grid-2">
      <div>
        <h4>Formats that work</h4>
        <ul style="font-size:0.9rem;padding-left:1rem">
          <li><strong>LinkedIn carousel:</strong> $2.15 CPC (3-4x cheaper than video). Use for owner education.</li>
          <li><strong>LinkedIn document ads:</strong> "12-Page Membership Plan ROI Calculator" — best B2B SaaS lead magnet right now.</li>
          <li><strong>Facebook lookalikes</strong> off Clerri's 5,000-practice CRM: lowest CPA ($25-75 dental Facebook benchmark).</li>
          <li>Podcast pre-roll on Nifty Thrifty / Bulletproof Dental.</li>
          <li>Retargeting visitors with case-study video.</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      <div>
        <h4>Targeting layers</h4>
        <ul style="font-size:0.9rem;padding-left:1rem">
          <li><strong>Job titles:</strong> Dentist, Owner Dentist, DDS, DMD, Practice Owner, Practice Manager</li>
          <li><strong>Company size:</strong> 1-10 employees (independent)</li>
          <li><strong>Industry:</strong> "Hospitals and Health Care"</li>
          <li><strong>EXCLUDE:</strong> students, freelancers, BD/Sales, non-ICP seniority (saves 20-35% LinkedIn benchmark)</li>
          <li><strong>Intent signals:</strong> visited DentalHQ, BoomCloud, Plan Forward pages (LinkedIn website retargeting)</li>
          <li><strong>Lookalike sources:</strong> Clerri's 5,000-practice CRM upload</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>

    <h4>Creative tropes to test</h4>
    <div data-section="ad-strategy">
      <label class="task"><input type="checkbox" data-track="creative-01-owner-testimonial" data-section="ad-strategy" /><div class="task-content"><div class="task-title">Dentist-spouse testimonial video — owner + spouse talking about "we did the math"</div></div></label>
      <label class="task"><input type="checkbox" data-track="creative-02-roi-doc" data-section="ad-strategy" /><div class="task-content"><div class="task-title">"The 12-Page Membership ROI Calculator" — LinkedIn document ad lead magnet</div></div></label>
      <label class="task"><input type="checkbox" data-track="creative-03-ppo-math" data-section="ad-strategy" /><div class="task-content"><div class="task-title">"$3-6M lifetime PPO write-off" carousel with calculator embed</div></div></label>
      <label class="task"><input type="checkbox" data-track="creative-04-fb-lookalike" data-section="ad-strategy" /><div class="task-content"><div class="task-title">Facebook lookalike off CRM — test against LinkedIn for SMB owner segment CPA</div></div></label>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- PERSONA 2: GROUP OPERATOR -->
  <h2>Persona 02 · <em>Group Practice Operator</em></h2>
  <div class="card">
    <p><strong>Profile:</strong> 5-25 locations. Often PE-backed or owner-led roll-up. Has a Director of Operations or VP Ops. Multi-location ops chaos — billing, comms, plans, payroll fragmented. Membership infrastructure is now a board-level question, not a nice-to-have.</p>

    <h4>Pain hooks</h4>
    <ul style="padding-left:1rem">
      <li>"Your 12 locations have 11 different membership configurations. Audit nightmare."</li>
      <li>"Roll-up acquisition? Members travel between your locations. <strong>Single platform or member churn.</strong>"</li>
      <li>"You're at the size where in-house billing breaks. Recurring billing infrastructure is non-negotiable."</li>
      <li>"PPO renegotiation leverage shrinks every year. Membership is your only owned channel."</li>
    </ul>

    <div class="grid-2">
      <div>
        <h4>Formats</h4>
        <ul style="font-size:0.9rem;padding-left:1rem">
          <li>Single-image LinkedIn with multi-location dashboard screenshot</li>
          <li>Document ads — "ROI calc per-location" or "Multi-Location Membership Audit"</li>
          <li>Co-branded webinars with state dental associations or Group Dentistry Now</li>
          <li>Podcast sponsorships on GDN Show (DSO-focused)</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      <div>
        <h4>Targeting</h4>
        <ul style="font-size:0.9rem;padding-left:1rem">
          <li>Titles: Director of Operations, VP Ops, Regional Manager, COO</li>
          <li>Company size 5-50</li>
          <li>Geographic clustering for trade show follow-up</li>
          <li>Industry: "Hospitals and Health Care" + group practice/multi-location</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div data-section="ad-strategy">
      <label class="task"><input type="checkbox" data-track="creative-05-multi-loc-audit" data-section="ad-strategy" /><div class="task-content"><div class="task-title">"Multi-Location Membership Audit" lead magnet — LinkedIn document ad</div></div></label>
      <label class="task"><input type="checkbox" data-track="creative-06-gdn-webinar" data-section="ad-strategy" /><div class="task-content"><div class="task-title">Co-host webinar with Group Dentistry Now — DSO ops focus</div></div></label>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- PERSONA 3: DSO EXECUTIVE -->
  <h2>Persona 03 · <em>DSO Executive</em></h2>
  <div class="card">
    <p><strong>Profile:</strong> 50+ locations. CEO, CMO, CFO, COO, Chief Growth Officer, VP Payor Operations, Chief Strategy Officer. PE-backed (KKR, Bain, etc.). NRR-obsessed. Boards care about category leadership and exit multiples. Specific named-account marketing is the only thing they notice.</p>

    <h4>Pain hooks</h4>
    <ul style="padding-left:1rem">
      <li>"You're powering Aspen's $49/yr plan (already on Clerri). <strong>Your DSO is one feature behind.</strong>"</li>
      <li>"PPO renegotiation leverage shrinks every year. Membership is the only owned channel."</li>
      <li>"<strong>Charlesbank backs Clerri.</strong> Your PE backers know the moat."</li>
      <li>"7 of the top 10 DSOs already run membership on Clerri. We benchmark your performance against them quarterly."</li>
    </ul>

    <div class="grid-2">
      <div>
        <h4>Formats</h4>
        <ul style="font-size:0.9rem;padding-left:1rem">
          <li><strong>Named-account LinkedIn single-image ads</strong> ("Heartland, here's how 7 of the top 10 DSOs run membership")</li>
          <li>Executive thought-leadership content from Jim/CEO on LinkedIn</li>
          <li>Podcast guest spots on Group Dentistry Now Show (Bill Neumann/Kim Larson — #1 DSO podcast)</li>
          <li>Trade show keynotes at ADSO Summit + DEO Intensive</li>
          <li>Becker's Dental + GDN earned editorial</li>
          <li>Charlesbank portfolio company introductions</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      <div>
        <h4>Targeting</h4>
        <ul style="font-size:0.9rem;padding-left:1rem">
          <li>Titles: CEO, CMO, CFO, COO, VP Marketing, Chief Growth Officer, VP Payor Operations, Chief Strategy Officer</li>
          <li>Specific company list: top-30 DSOs from Becker's</li>
          <li>LinkedIn matched-audience upload of named accounts</li>
          <li>Industry: "Hospitals and Health Care"</li>
          <li>Intent signals: visited Clerri pricing/comparison pages, downloaded ROI calculator</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div data-section="ad-strategy">
      <label class="task"><input type="checkbox" data-track="creative-07-named-dso" data-section="ad-strategy" /><div class="task-content"><div class="task-title">Named-account LinkedIn campaigns for Heartland, PDS Health, Smile Brands (top displacement targets)</div></div></label>
      <label class="task"><input type="checkbox" data-track="creative-08-gdn-podcast" data-section="ad-strategy" /><div class="task-content"><div class="task-title">Get the CEO or John on Group Dentistry Now Show (Bill Neumann)</div></div></label>
      <label class="task"><input type="checkbox" data-track="creative-09-jim-linkedin" data-section="ad-strategy" /><div class="task-content"><div class="task-title">Jim LinkedIn content cadence — peer-set thought leadership (NOT product marketing)</div></div></label>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- COMPETITOR AD CAMPAIGNS WORTH STUDYING -->
  <h2>Competitor campaigns worth <em>studying.</em></h2>
  <p style="color:var(--ink-soft);max-width:65ch">Five real campaigns from competitors and adjacent dental SaaS. Steal what works, avoid what's stale.</p>

  <div class="grid-2">
    <div class="card">
      <h4>01 · BoomCloud "Recurring Revenue Machine" content suite</h4>
      <p style="font-size:0.9rem;color:var(--ink-soft)">Full-funnel blog → guide → podcast (Automatic Patient + Say No to PPOs). <strong>100% organic / content-led.</strong> Comstock is on the podcast circuit relentlessly.</p>
      <p class="mono" style="font-size:0.75rem;color:var(--clerri-green)">Lesson: Founder thought-leadership compounds. Clerri needs Jim out-podcasting Comstock.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="card">
      <h4>02 · DentalHQ Nifty Thrifty placement</h4>
      <p style="font-size:0.9rem;color:var(--ink-soft)">"Uncomplicating Dentistry" episode with Glenn Vo. Endorsement-style positioning. Vendor-discount model.</p>
      <p class="mono" style="font-size:0.75rem;color:var(--clerri-green)">Lesson: Glenn Vo's pay-for-deal model is lowest-CPL in dental. Clerri should test a Deal-of-the-Month.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="card">
      <h4>03 · Plan Forward / AADOM Featured Company</h4>
      <p style="font-size:0.9rem;color:var(--ink-soft)">30-minute interview format. <strong>$5-10K placement range typical.</strong> Lohman owns this channel.</p>
      <p class="mono" style="font-size:0.75rem;color:var(--clerri-green)">Lesson: AADOM Featured Company is a sticky earned-media format. Clerri should buy one + supply customer voices.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="card">
      <h4>04 · Aspen Dental Savings Plan consumer ads</h4>
      <p style="font-size:0.9rem;color:var(--ink-soft)">Public-facing $49/yr plan ads. <strong>Membersy-powered</strong> — demonstrates the end-customer creative pattern Clerri's DSO partners already deploy.</p>
      <p class="mono" style="font-size:0.75rem;color:var(--clerri-green)">Lesson: We have the consumer-side creative chassis already. Apply it to the patient directory launch.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="card">
      <h4>05 · Subscribili funding-wave PR (Feb 2024)</h4>
      <p style="font-size:0.9rem;color:var(--ink-soft)">Earned coverage across DentistryToday, BusinessWire, Built In Austin, DPR on a single $4.3M seed.</p>
      <p class="mono" style="font-size:0.75rem;color:var(--clerri-green)">Lesson: Dental press will syndicate news widely. Plan PR-worthy announcements quarterly to maintain category presence.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="card">
      <h4>06 · Hint Health DPC Trends Report (annual)</h4>
      <p style="font-size:0.9rem;color:var(--ink-soft)">Annual State of DPC report + Hint Summit. <strong>Own the category data narrative.</strong> Adjacent membership infrastructure play.</p>
      <p class="mono" style="font-size:0.75rem;color:var(--clerri-green)">Lesson: Clerri should publish an annual "State of Dental Membership" report — Year 1 deliverable.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- INFLUENCER / PODCAST PRICING -->
  <h2>Dental influencer &amp; podcast <em>sponsorship pricing.</em></h2>
  <p style="color:var(--ink-soft);max-width:65ch">No competitor publishes rates. Estimates triangulated from B2B SaaS benchmarks + dental industry patterns. Confidence flagged per row.</p>

  <div style="overflow-x:auto">
    <table class="data-table">
      <thead><tr><th>Channel</th><th>Format</th><th>Est. Cost</th><th>Confidence</th><th>Notes</th></tr></thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr><td><strong>Glenn Vo / Nifty Thrifty</strong></td><td>Podcast + Facebook group + website placement</td><td class="num-cell">$5-15K package</td><td><span class="pill pill-grey">Low</span></td><td>Vendor-funded model; promo codes + affiliate revenue share. Contact: Glenn Vo directly.</td></tr>
        <tr><td><strong>Group Dentistry Now Show</strong> (Bill Neumann/Kim Larson)</td><td>Host-read sponsorship</td><td class="num-cell">$1-3K / episode</td><td><span class="pill pill-zest">Medium</span></td><td>#1 DSO podcast. B2B niche CPM $50-100 benchmark. Highest-fit for DSO ICP.</td></tr>
        <tr><td><strong>Bulletproof Dental Practice</strong> (Boulden/Spodak)</td><td>Host-read biweekly</td><td class="num-cell">$1-2K / episode</td><td><span class="pill pill-grey">Low</span></td><td>425 episodes, 9 years. Owner audience. Has Bulletproof Summit annual event.</td></tr>
        <tr><td><strong>Dental A Team</strong> (Kiera Dent)</td><td>Host-read 3x/week</td><td class="num-cell">$750-1.5K / episode</td><td><span class="pill pill-zest">Medium</span></td><td>933 episodes, high-volume = lower per-episode CPM.</td></tr>
        <tr><td><strong>Dentistry Uncensored</strong> (Howard Farran)</td><td>Host-read</td><td class="num-cell">No published rate</td><td><span class="pill pill-zest">Contact verified</span></td><td>1,500+ episodes, 8M+ downloads. Contact: Sally Gross at Farran Media. sally@farranmedia.com</td></tr>
        <tr><td><strong>AADOM Featured Company</strong></td><td>30-min interview + AADOM Radio Ep</td><td class="num-cell">$5-10K placement</td><td><span class="pill pill-zest">Medium</span></td><td>Plan Forward uses this — Lohman is on AADOM Radio Ep 115. Buy adjacent placements.</td></tr>
        <tr><td><strong>B2B SaaS podcast benchmark</strong></td><td>18 episodes across 4-5 shows</td><td class="num-cell">$8.5-25K campaign</td><td><span class="pill pill-zest">Medium</span></td><td>~$470-1,390/episode CPM benchmark.</td></tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
  </div>

  <div class="callout">
    <div class="lbl">Recommended podcast portfolio · 6 months</div>
    <p>Buy 3 podcasts concurrent: <strong>Group Dentistry Now Show</strong> (DSO ICP) + <strong>Bulletproof Dental Practice</strong> (owner audience) + <strong>Nifty Thrifty</strong> (lowest CPL via Glenn Vo deal-of-the-month). Budget: $5-8K/month combined. Test against Google Ads CAC after 90 days.</p>
  </div>

  <div data-section="ad-strategy">
    <label class="task"><input type="checkbox" data-track="creative-10-podcast-portfolio" data-section="ad-strategy" /><div class="task-content"><div class="task-title">Lock 3-podcast 6-month portfolio: GDN Show + Bulletproof + Nifty Thrifty</div></div></label>
    <label class="task"><input type="checkbox" data-track="creative-11-glenn-vo-deal" data-section="ad-strategy" /><div class="task-content"><div class="task-title">Negotiate Glenn Vo Nifty Thrifty "Deal of the Month" — promo-code-driven trackable CPL</div></div></label>
    <label class="task"><input type="checkbox" data-track="creative-12-aadom-featured" data-section="ad-strategy" /><div class="task-content"><div class="task-title">Book AADOM Featured Company placement — counter-balance Plan Forward's hold on this channel</div></div></label>
    <label class="task"><input type="checkbox" data-track="creative-13-state-of-report" data-section="ad-strategy" /><div class="task-content"><div class="task-title">Year-1 deliverable: "State of Dental Membership 2027" report (Hint Health pattern)</div></div></label>
  </div>

  <div class="note-block">
    <div class="note-label">Creative testing notes <span class="note-saved">✓ saved</span></div>
    <textarea data-note="ad-strategy-testing" placeholder="What converts, what doesn't, CPL by creative, A/B test results, what Jim/sales team gives feedback on..."></textarea>
  </div>

  <div class="topic-foot">
    <a href="/clerri/icp"><span class="dir">← Prev</span><span class="name">05 · ICP & ABM</span></a>
    <a href="/clerri/aeo-seo"><span class="dir">Next →</span><span class="name">07 · AEO / SEO / SEM</span></a>
  </div>

</div>
</ClerriLayout>
